4. OUTPUT STRATEGY MATRIX DESIGN
================================================================================

This section proposes a design for supporting arbitrary input → output format
combinations, addressing FINDING-01.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4.1 Current State
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Input Format   Output Formats    Status
  ───────────────────────────────────────
  Markdown (.md) html              READY
  Markdown (.md) pdf               READY
  Markdown (.md) docx              READY
  All others     All               NOT SUPPORTED

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4.2 Proposed Output Strategy Matrix
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Input Format   Output Format    Pandoc From    Engine          Priority
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  markdown       html             markdown       pandoc          P0 (done)
  markdown       pdf              markdown       pandoc+tectonic P0 (done)
  markdown       docx             markdown       pandoc          P0 (done)
  markdown       epub             markdown       pandoc          P1
  markdown       latex            markdown       pandoc          P1
  markdown       rst              markdown       pandoc          P2
  markdown       plain            markdown       pandoc          P2
  markdown       slides (revealjs)markdown       pandoc          P2
  markdown       slides (beamer)  markdown       pandoc+tectonic P2
  docx           html             docx           pandoc          P1
  docx           pdf              docx           pandoc+tectonic P1
  docx           markdown         docx           pandoc          P1
  html           pdf              html           pandoc+tectonic P1
  html           markdown         html           pandoc          P2
  epub           html             epub           pandoc          P2
  epub           pdf              epub           pandoc+tectonic P2
  rst            html             rst            pandoc          P2
  rst            pdf              rst            pandoc+tectonic P2
  latex          pdf              latex          tectonic/pdflatex P1
  odt            html/pdf/docx    odt            pandoc          P3

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4.3 Recommended Architecture for Multi-Format Support
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Step 1 — Add InputFormat type to config.rs:

  pub enum InputFormat {
      Markdown,
      Docx,
      Html,
      Epub,
      Rst,
      Latex,
      // ... auto-detected from file extension when not specified
  }

  impl Config {
      pub fn input_format(&self) -> InputFormat {
          InputFormat::from_extension(&self.input)
              .unwrap_or(InputFormat::Markdown)
      }
  }

Step 2 — Pass InputFormat to select_strategy():

  pub fn select_strategy(
      input_format: InputFormat,
      output_type: OutputType,
      template: Option<String>,
      template_dir: String,
  ) -> Result<Box<dyn OutputStrategy>>

  Each strategy implementation reads self.input_format to set the
  pandoc --from flag dynamically.

Step 3 — Validate compatibility at config load time:

  Add a compatibility matrix check in Config::validate():

    fn is_supported_combination(input: &InputFormat, output: &OutputType) -> bool {
        // ...
    }

  Return a clear error when an unsupported combination is requested:
  "Input format 'epub' → output format 'docx' is not yet supported."

Step 4 — Expose in YAML config (backward-compatible):

  input: "document.docx"
  input_format: docx        # optional — auto-detected from extension
  outputs:
    - type: html
    - type: pdf

  The input_format key defaults to auto-detection, preserving backward
  compatibility for existing renderflow.yaml files.

