12. SUGGESTED FIXES (PRIORITISED)
================================================================================

PRIORITY 1 — Immediate (low effort, high value):

  FIX-01 → addresses FINDING-10: Cache transform output
    Move register_transforms().apply_all() outside the per-format loop.
    Effort: 5 minutes. Impact: eliminates redundant transform work.

  FIX-02 → addresses FINDING-11: Update README for DOCX
    Add docx to the Supported Output Types table.
    Remove "DOCX output format" from the Roadmap.
    Add `variables` to the Configuration section.
    Effort: 30 minutes. Impact: documentation accuracy.

  FIX-03 → addresses FINDING-09: Remove or integrate PandocStep
    Delete src/pipeline/pandoc_step.rs if it is not used.
    Or refactor strategies to use it as a shared pandoc invocation helper.
    Effort: 30 minutes. Impact: removes dead code confusion.

PRIORITY 2 — Short term (medium effort, high value):

  FIX-04 → addresses FINDING-03: Unify Pipeline / TransformRegistry entry point
    Refactor Pipeline to hold a TransformRegistry and delegate run_transforms().
    Or remove Pipeline::run_transforms() and document the usage pattern.
    Effort: 2 hours. Impact: cleaner API, removes dead code warning.

  FIX-05 → addresses FINDING-06: Make EmojiTransform format-aware
    Skip emoji replacement for html output. Apply only for pdf/docx/latex.
    Effort: 2 hours (requires OutputType in transform context).
    Impact: documents with emoji render correctly in HTML.

  FIX-06 → addresses FINDING-08: Code-block-aware variable substitution
    Parse the input to identify code spans and fenced code blocks, and skip
    variable substitution inside them.
    Effort: 4 hours. Impact: prevents corruption of code examples.

  FIX-07 → addresses FINDING-07: Validate PDF/DOCX templates upfront
    Check for template file existence for all output types at the start of
    the build command, not just HTML templates via Tera.
    Effort: 2 hours. Impact: earlier, clearer error messages.

PRIORITY 3 — Medium term (higher effort, strategic value):

  FIX-08 → addresses FINDING-01: Add InputFormat abstraction
    Implement InputFormat enum, auto-detection from file extension, and
    config validation for supported input/output combinations.
    Effort: 1-2 days. Impact: enables full output strategy matrix.

  FIX-09 → addresses FINDING-02: Pandoc AST as intermediate representation
    Use pandoc --to json to produce an AST, apply transforms on the AST,
    then convert to each output format with pandoc --from json.
    Effort: 3-5 days. Impact: single-parse multi-output, richer transforms.

  FIX-10 → addresses FINDING-05: Parallel output rendering
    Use Rayon to render independent output formats concurrently.
    Effort: 4-8 hours (including thread-safe progress bar).
    Impact: 2-3× speedup for multi-format configs.

================================================================================
13. POSITIVE OBSERVATIONS
================================================================================

OBSERVATION-01: Transform Registry is production-quality
  The TransformRegistry implementation is robust: fail-fast / continue mode,
  per-transform named error context, DEBUG-level lifecycle logging, and
  comprehensive unit tests. This is a well-engineered component.

OBSERVATION-02: Partial-failure resilience preserved
  commands/build.rs continues rendering all output formats even when one
  fails, collecting errors and reporting them together at the end. This is
  user-friendly and correct behaviour.

OBSERVATION-03: Template path resolution is safe and tested
  All three strategies (Html, Pdf, Docx) check for template file existence
  before invoking pandoc, returning a clear error message. The "Template file
  not found" error identifies the full path, making it immediately actionable.

OBSERVATION-04: Config validation is early and comprehensive
  Config::validate() checks input non-empty, outputs non-empty, and collects
  all unsupported output types in a single error. Users see every problem at
  once rather than fixing one at a time.

OBSERVATION-05: Asset path normalisation is robust
  normalize_asset_paths() handles relative paths, absolute paths, four URL
  schemes, inline title attributes, and malformed/incomplete image syntax.
  The test coverage is thorough with 12 test cases covering edge cases.

OBSERVATION-06: Cargo.lock is now tracked in VCS
  The previous audit identified the missing Cargo.lock as a critical issue.
  This has been resolved — Cargo.lock is now committed, ensuring reproducible
  builds across environments.

OBSERVATION-07: DOCX strategy completes the core format trio
  The DocxStrategy implementation follows the same pattern as HtmlStrategy
  and PdfStrategy, uses the correct pandoc flag (--reference-doc instead of
  --template), and has full unit test coverage. This is a clean addition.

OBSERVATION-08: Three registered transforms with correct ordering
  The standard transform pipeline (emoji → variable → syntax) is correctly
  ordered and consistent: emoji replacement happens before variable
  substitution, preventing {{...}} patterns in emoji alt text from being
  expanded. The ordering is documented in register_transforms().

================================================================================
14. SYSTEM READINESS
================================================================================

Status: READY (with noted limitations)

The core md → html / pdf / docx rendering pipeline is production-ready. The
codebase is well-tested, follows consistent patterns, has good error handling,
and the key issues from the previous audit (Cargo.lock, template wiring, dead
code, DOCX) have been addressed.

The READY status acknowledges the following current limitations:
  - Input format is hardcoded to Markdown (FINDING-01)
  - No plugin/extension system for user-defined transforms (FINDING-04)
  - Output rendering is sequential — no parallelism (FINDING-05)
  - EmojiTransform is unconditionally lossy (FINDING-06)
  - Documentation does not fully reflect current capabilities (FINDING-11)

Recommended actions for the next evolution cycle:

  [ ] FIX-01: Cache transform output (5 minutes)
  [ ] FIX-02: Update README for DOCX and variables (30 minutes)
  [ ] FIX-03: Remove or integrate PandocStep (30 minutes)
  [ ] FIX-04: Unify Pipeline / TransformRegistry (2 hours)
  [ ] FIX-05: Format-aware EmojiTransform (2 hours)
  [ ] FIX-06: Code-block-aware variable substitution (4 hours)
  [ ] FIX-08: InputFormat abstraction (1-2 days)
  [ ] FIX-10: Parallel output rendering (4-8 hours)

Strategic recommendations for next major version:
  [ ] Pandoc AST as intermediate representation (FIX-09)
  [ ] Shell-based transform plugin system (Section 11.1 Phase 1)
  [ ] Unified template registry (Section 11.2 TEMPLATE-01)
  [ ] Watch mode with incremental rebuilds (Section 11.4 ORCH-02)

